Upon completion of this analysis this evidence will be stored at the Maryland State Police, Frederick Barrack B Property Room pending trial. NARRATIVE: On 01/03/2023, at 2254 hours, I (TFC Blumenauer #6357) was on-duty in marked Maryland State Police vehicle B-66 in the area of northbound Maryland Route 194 (Woodsboro Pike) at Adventure Avenue in Walkersville, Frederick County, Maryland, working routine patrol. At this time, I observed a silver 2013 Hyundai Sonata bearing Maryland state registration 2EJ2904, traveling in the northbound lane of Maryland Route 194 (Woodsboro Pike), directly in front of my patrol vehicle, at Adventure Avenue. The vehicle grabbed my attention when I observed the vehicles drivers side brake light was inoperable. After observing the violation, I then activated my emergency equipment, and conducted a traffic stop on the vehicle. The vehicle came to final rest on Adventure Avenue at Maryland Route 194 (Woodsboro Pike). I approached the vehicle via the passenger side window. I then identified the operator, by her Maryland learners permit as Jessica Marie Queen (DOB 06/20/2006). I then identified the front seat passenger by her Maryland drivers license as Allison Taylor Queen (DOB 10/07/1998). Upon speaking with the vehicle occupants, I detected an extremely strong odor of burnt marijuana emanating from the interior vehicle. I was able to identify the smell of marijuana based on my training, knowledge, and experience as a Maryland State Trooper. I advised dispatch that I would be conducting a probable cause search on the Hyundai. At approximately 2306 hours, Sgt. Lantz #1981, arrived on scene to assist. The vehicle search began at 2307 hours. The search took approximately 15 minutes. From the result of the search the following item(s) were located: One (1) grey metal grinder containing a greenish brown vegetable matter of suspected raw marijuana. (Item A), which was located in the center console of the vehicle. It should be noted Allison Queen took ownership of all of the contraband located. It should be noted Allison Queen was polite and cooperative throughout the process. Allison Queen was released with one (1) civil citation related to the traffic stop. Jessica Queen was issued one (1) safety equipment repair order (SERO) related to the traffic stop. Copies of all documents were added to the attachments section of this report. All of the above events occurred in Frederick County, Maryland. CHARGES: CR 5-601(a)(1) CDS: Possession Marijuana: Less than 10 grams (CJIS # 1_0573) CASE STATUS: Case closed by civil citation.
